tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, suggesting impaired renal function and possible nephrotic syndrome or acute kidney injury. Low HbA1c with normal glucose may indicate recent hypoglycemia or anemia. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal) and low specific gravity further support renal dysfunction. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and further assessment for underlying causes.
